11. Testing Approach
Manual testing by inputting different index values and verifying the correctness of the output sequences for each scenario.​

12. Challenges Faced
Handling large indices efficiently.

Designing logic for various index ranges to avoid calculation errors.

13. Learnings & Key Takeaways
Importance of control structures for sequence logic.

How to implement digit manipulation algorithms within procedural programming.

14. Future Enhancements
Add graphical user interface.

Optimize algorithm for extremely large indices.

Implement additional sequence types (e.g., prime number concatenation).

